@Node 1 " Introduction "

What is Master Empire?
----------------------

  Master Empire is probably the most comprehensive Arexx Door you will
find for the MEBBSNET © BBS package!  Actually, its not THAT spectacular.
I'm writing this doc file by using my .GUIDE from BBS Rolodex and just
changing the pertinent info.  Its a lot easier than starting from scratch ;)


  Features include:


a.  Multiplayer Multiline Game

b.  Autodetecting ANSI/ASCII

c.  If you have HANDLES turned on, it offers their current handle as the
    handle to use in the game.  They can of course choose another.

d.  A fun lotto subgame after each turn.

  
@EndNode
@Node 2 " Why use Master Empire? "
Why use Master Empire instead of other similar programs?
--------------------------------------------------------


--- Its a fun game! ;)

--- It works!

--- Fully supported by  @{" LARRY CLOUD " Link 14} , a @{" MEBBSNET © CSR Site " Link 15}

--- Extremely @{" CONFIGURABLE " Link 3}


@EndNode
@Node 3 " How do I configure Master Empire? " 
How do I configure Master Empire?
---------------------------------

Master Empire is an AREXX © script for the MEBBSNET © BBS software.  You must
already have AREXX © @{"installed and running" Link 16} prior to attempting
to run this door.

Once that prerequisite is met, you need to @{"make a MENU entry" Link 17} that allows
users to access it from a menu (you can't use @{"DOORS.CFG" Link 18}).

Then you need to make a subdirectory off of DOORS: and call it MEMPIRE.
See your AMIGADOS manual if you don't know how to make a directory.

Next, bring the MASEMP.CFG file into a text editor (NOT a word processor!) and
edit it to your liking.  Press @{"This Button" Link 21} to see an example of
the configuration file for this door.

If you'd like to know how to edit the STATS file, press @{"This Button" Link 12} now.

@EndNode
@Node 12 "Editing Stats File"

CHEATER CHEATER!  Now that that emotional outburst is over, the stats are laid
out as follows:
A B
C D E F G H I J K L M N O P Q

Where:

A=Max Players In the Game  B=Current # Of Players In Game

C=Land  D=Troops  E=Serfs  F=Nobles  G=Grain  H=Cash  I=Tax Rate

J=% Of Palace (1=10%)  K=Markets  L=Mills  M=Foundrys  N=Shipyards

O=Alive? (1=Yes)  P=Plays Taken Today  Q=Days Of Protection Left


Heres an example STATS file.

50 4
PENNYWISE CLOWN
PENNYWISE CLOWN
3813244 380240 7127 19162 6687732 10000000 2 9 30032 50010 20146 55172 1 1 0
BULGARIA
THE MAN
5000 20 2322 10 25000 25000 15 1 10 10 10 10 1 0 8
JAMMIN
ANDRE
5000 20 2262 10 25000 25000 15 1 10 10 10 10 1 0 8
DARTH VADER
KING
5000 20 2201 10 25000 25000 15 1 10 10 10 10 1 0 8

@endnode

@Node 4 " What files are required? "
Required Files
--------------

All the files included in the archive are required.  If you are installing
this version as an UPGRADE, click this button @{"UPDATE INFO" Link 19} now, then
return here.

As of version 5.1, I have decided to compile the source to increase speed.
You MUST unarchive the REXXPLUS.LHA archive that is included in this archive.

Next, install the RPSTART program in your WBSTARTUP drawer, the
rexxplslib.library in your LIBS: drawer, and the RPHI in your C: drawer.

Be sure to @{"configure" link 3} the door to customize the setup for your BBS.

For program OPERATION, there is a file called (get this) INSTRUCTIONS.TXT.
This file is shown while in the door and the user asks for instructions.
Click on @{"THIS BUTTON" link 22} to read it.

@EndNode

@Node 5 " Updates "
Updates To Master Empire
