@Node 16 "Installing / Running Arexx"
Installing Arexx
----------------

This door REQUIRES the use of AmigaDos 2.04 or higher.  Since thats the case, AREXX
should already be installed and running in our system, unless you specifically took
it out of your startup scripts.  If thats the case, see your AMIGADOS manual for
instructions on re-installing AREXX on your system.  This door will NOT work
without the AREXX server being active.

@EndNode

@Node 17 "Menu Entry"
Whats The Menu Entry Look Like?
-------------------------------

You'll need to make an entry in one or more of your menus that looks like the
example below.  You can use any valid keystroke (I used Z in my example).

Option 'Z':
    Function Arexx doors:MEMPIRE/MASEMP
    end

Once you make this change, recompile the menu with MENUCOMPILER.

@EndNode

@Node 18 "DOORS.CFG"
Why Can't I Use DOORS.CFG for this door?
----------------------------------------

DOORS.CFG is not set up to run AREXX scripts.  You can ONLY run AREXX scripts from
a standard @{"MENU ENTRY" Link 17}.

@EndNode

@Node 19 "Update Info"
What Has Changed In This Version?
---------------------------------

This is the place to look to see what has changed in this door.  It will tell you
whether you need to just install the executable (MASEMP.REXX) or other
portions of the archive as well.  If this is the first time you have set up the
door, you MUST install the COMPLETE archive!


Changes
-------

5.1
---

Executable has changed.

Compiled the code and fixed reported bugs (that I could FIND!).  Be sure to
read the CONFIGURATION section of this document.

If you have a problem with Master Empire, be sure to send in a @{"bug report" link 8}.

See @{"HISTORY" Link 11} for info on previous versions.

@EndNode

@Node 20 "For The Curious"
Whats This Button Do?
---------------------

AHA!  I put something in here!  If you want to "cheat" on someone elses game (like
you call someone out of state or something), set your TAX RATE to 2% and then use
the vertical bar key "|" at any "Press Any Key To Continue" prompt.  Gives ya grunches
of money!

See it DOES pay to look at ALL the docs!

@EndNode

